    "description": {
      "value": "<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.86KAswzvW059QBvd]{UM5 Ch.6: Vehicle Rules} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.Y1Gd46S0jlbBpdeR]{UM5 Ch.6: Vehicle Modifications}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.F6cQvEDkEhpqIIqA]{UM5 Ch.6: Vehicle Statistics, Aircraft}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.p9fpWIpzZ6UvzzED]{UM5 Ch.6: Vehicle Statistics, Ground Vehicles}&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.oW9iuEoxWvtPKvDo]{UM5 Ch.6: Tech Level 0-5}</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">A vehicle must have a listed hit point total equal to or&nbsp;greater than 30 to mount a two-handed weapon turret,&nbsp;equal to or greater than 60 to mount a heavy weapon&nbsp;(unless stated otherwise), and equal to or greater than&nbsp;100 to mount a super heavy weapon (unless stated otherwise). Most vehicles can have only one weapon&nbsp;mount. Weapons use their original size when determining what can be fitted to a mount, even if they nominally count as a smaller weapon for a larger user.</p>\n<table class=\"NormalTable\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 242px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Weapon mount (2-handed small-arm) </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 36px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">500 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 25px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">1 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">—</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 242px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Weapon Turret (heavy weapon) </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 36px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">2,500 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 25px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">1 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">—</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 242px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Weapon Turret (super heavy weapon) </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 36px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">6,500 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 25px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">1 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">—</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
